and fast cuting animated fighting sceens are now becoming a must for a good anime. I have been working on hours of wasted concept art for characters for 3d realtime animestyle animation ^_^. <br>
<br>
What i would like to know is instead of me working on a super long time on a decent story line, would you rather just seen fighting sceens or just a bunch of reading text (no voices will be added to the animation, maybe sound).<br>
<br>
Also if you like just fighting sceens what kinda of characters would you expect to see? Heavy Mecha style armor, or a bit of midevil style cothing....<br>
<br>
Heres a bit of a note, creating fighting sceen in 3d is one thing but creating them in realtime animation is another because quickly jumping from one sceen to another is not easy on the cpu. So a lot fo the modeling job would have to be lowpoly stuff.<br>
<br>
And a bit of help i am requesting, becuase creating a simple 3d screen is not really that easy, due to the fact of creating textures I was hoping to mix 2d backgrounds and maybe someone who could draw bgs maybe could give me a few pointers on creating them.<br>
<br>
Last question is would you rather see guns or swords? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=prismrefraction>PrismRefraction</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/18/02 4:23:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1762.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Key pointing in interest of Anime?</span><hr size=1> Story.  Story good, thats' why msot people who play RPGs don't give a crap about the level of detail... they jsut care about the story. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ustaby.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Staby</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/18/02 5:22:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1762.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Story</span><hr size=1> Ok one good vote on story ^_^, ill start working on it right away!<br>
::Sutabi (aka Staby) opens up Word Perfect and burns the keyboard up with rapid keystorkes:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utaerx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TaerX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/18/02 5:53:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1762.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Key pointing in interest of Anime?</span><hr size=1> Guns vs. swords is negligible.  Whatever's appropriate for the story.<br>
<br>
Yep, it's that darned s-word again.  I remember good stories, not good fights.  I've seen a few decent fights in movies, but don't remember the details off the top of my head because I felt the story was bad.  In contrast, I can describe many of the fights from <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Aliens</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> The Killer</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, or <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Crouching Tiger, Hidden Dragon</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> because the whole movie was memorable.  <br>
<br>
Well, watching the films multiple times helps too.  But what makes me want to watch a movie multiple times?  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> A good story.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Most anime fans I know prefer subbed movies, but I'm an 0ld5K0013r.  Still, given that demographic, I wouldn't mind reading my way through a story, inbetween the 'money shots' - the scenes you spend effort rendering.<br>
<br>
I have to confess, I do remember a few fight-scene 'money shots', but not for the violence.  Specifically, I remember the ending from <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Riding Bean</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> for the ... what I phrase <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> gun-fu</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> - where it's obvious someone studied the properties of a weapon and uses it in a novel, yet plausible way. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ustaby.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Staby</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/18/02 6:14:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1762.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   thanks again!</span><hr size=1> Heh ok that helped much more! I am basing my story around mecha since i have not really drawn to much mecha i want to try something new. In a week I should have a somewhat decent storyline for the first show ^_^. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uotakulad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>OtakuLad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Canadian <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/18/02 7:26:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1762.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.calgarymedia.com/asuka.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: thanks again!</span><hr size=1> Audience.<br>
