http://www.soundclick.com/oursin</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubanishedknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Banished Knight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/19/02 2:36:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1762.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://liquid2k.com/banishedknight/Sephiroth WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Key pointing in interest of Anime?</span><hr size=1> um, well it depends on the genre of anime.  In my opinion, a really good balance of action and story makes the perfect anime ((assuming it's supposed to have action in it as part of the storyline)).  Finding that perfect balance is very VERY difficult and is rarely done,  but most of the great anime out there have come close and that's all there really is to it.  Develop characters that people can really get into, a storyline that can keep people wanting to know what's going to happen next, and some great action sequences and that's it.  Tying it all together is the hard part, at least to me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utimthewarrior777.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TimTheWarrior777</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/19/02 5:09:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1762.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Key pointing in interest of Anime?</span><hr size=1> I'm a martial artist so I like seeing fight's, but in a story the plot is far more important than the fight(Although flashy effects are nice). I didnt play Final Fantasy or Xenogears for the fights. Cowboy Bebop doesnt have many fights but it is a realy great Anime! The whole point of a drawing is to tell a story(Since a picture speaks a thousand words), thats why we have our charectors makeing expressions and standing in poses. Maybe there isnt even need for alot of speach, you could show things happen also.<br>
<br>
God bless!<br>
~Tim~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utiandogg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TianDogg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/19/02 6:46:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1762.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://3gclantrigun.clanpages.com/webpage/images/logos/Legato.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Key pointing in interest of Anime?</span><hr size=1> I personally prefer a strong storyline, but the fad nowadays with computer games and stuff is military style combat.  I haven't seen an anime pull that off well except Gasaraki, but even that had giant robots. <p><a href="http://3gclantrigun.clanpages.com"><img src="http://3gclantrigun.clanpages.com/webpage/images/logos/sig1.jpg" border=0></a><br><br>
Your role in the show is over.  The last act is about to begin.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uotakulad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>OtakuLad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Canadian <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/20/02 1:22:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1762.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.calgarymedia.com/asuka.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Key pointing in interest of Anime?</span><hr size=1> OK then, I'm a big believer in working within your limitations.<br>
<br>
No voice actors and 3D. Hmmm.....<br>
